import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.scatter(data['x'], data['y'])
    plt.title('What is the correlation between x and y coordinates?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('x')
    plt.ylabel('y')
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.hist(data['x'], bins=20)
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('What is the distribution of x coordinates?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
from scipy.spatial.distance import pdist, squareform

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    dist = pdist(data)
    plt.hist(dist, bins=20)
    plt.xlabel('Distance between points')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of the distance between points?', wrap=True)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.xticks(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import numpy as np

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['distance'] = np.sqrt(data['x'].diff()**2 + data['y'].diff()**2)
    plt.boxplot(data['distance'])
    plt.title('What is the average distance between points?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Distance')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
